title: Expedite Request Denied
body: On March 5, 2021, we denied your request for expedited processing of your I-765, Application for Employment Authorization, Receipt Number YSC2190063000. We do not believe, based on a review of your request, that your case meets one or more of the expedite criteria and otherwise merits expedited processing. We review all expedite requests on a case-by-case basis, and we grant them at the discretion of the director. Information regarding the USCIS expedite policy, including the expedite criteria, is available at www.uscis.gov/forms/expedite-criteria. If you move, go to www.uscis.gov/addresschange to give us your new mailing address.

Please follow the instructions in the notice. If you have any questions, contact the USCIS Contact Center at www.uscis.gov/contactcenter. If you move, go to www.uscis.gov/addresschange to give us your new mailing address.

title: Card Was Mailed To Me
body: On March 22, 2021, we mailed your new card for your Form I-765, Application for Employment Authorization, Receipt Number YSC2190063998, to the address you gave us. If you do not receive your card by April 6, 2021, please go to www.uscis.gov/e-request to request that we send your new card to you. If you move, go to www.uscis.gov/addresschange to give us your new mailing address.

title: Card Was Picked Up By The United States Postal Service
body: On March 22, 2021, the Post Office picked up mail containing your new card for Receipt Number YSC2190063999. We mailed your card to the address you gave us. The tracking number assigned is 9205590153708404134514. You can use your tracking number at www.USPS.com in the Quick Tools Tracking section. If you did not receive the card, please go to www.uscis.gov/e-request to request that we resend the card to you. If you move, go to www.uscis.gov/addresschange to give us your new mailing address.
